S&P 500 Futures Pare Gain on Caterpillar

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-07-22T11:45:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/s-p-500-index-futures-pare-advance-as-caterpillar-earnings-trail-estimates.html
U.S. stock futures trimmed gains
after Caterpillar Inc. reported earnings that trailed analysts’
estimates and said it is seeing a “softening of growth” in
 China .  Caterpillar, the world’s largest maker of construction
equipment, tumbled 4.3 percent.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index rose 0.1 percent
to 1,344.0 as of 7:45 a.m. in  New York  after climbing as much as
0.4 percent earlier. Dow Jones Industrial Average futures fell 8
points, or 0.1 percent, to 12,682, erasing a gain of as much as
0.5 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael P. Regan at 
 mregan12@bloomberg.net  